I14As used in this chapter, the term ``terrorist activity'' means any activity which is unlawful under the laws of the place where it is committed (or which, if it had been committed in the United States, would be unlawful under the laws of the United States or any State) and which involves any of the following:

I16(I) The highjacking or sabotage of any conveyance (including an aircraft, vessel, or vehicle).

