I89. Visa waiver program for certain visitors

I19(a) Establishment of program

I11The Attorney General and the Secretary of State are authorized to establish a program (hereinafter in this section referred to as the ``program'') under which the requirement of paragraph (7)(B)(i)(II) of section 1182(a) of this title may be waived by the Attorney General, in consultation with the Secretary of State and in accordance with this section, in the case of an alien who meets the following requirements:

I79(1) Seeking entry as tourist for 90 days or less

I12The alien is applying for admission during the program as a nonimmigrant visitor (described in section 1101(a)(15)(B) of this title) for a period not exceeding 90 days.

I79(2) National of program country

I12The alien is a national of, and presents a passport issued by, a country which_

I13(A) extends (or agrees to extend), either on its own or in conjunction with one or more other countries that are described in subparagraph (B) and that have established with it a common area for immigration admissions, reciprocal privileges to citizens and nationals of the United States, and

I13(B) is designated as a pilot program country under subsection (c) of this section.

I79(3) Machine readable passport

I18(A) In general

I13Except as provided in subparagraph (B), on or after October 1, 2003, the alien at the time of application for admission is in possession of a valid unexpired machine-readable passport that satisfies the internationally accepted standard for machine readability.

I18(B) Limited waiver authority

I13For the period beginning October 1, 2003, and ending September 30, 2007, the Secretary of State may waive the requirement of subparagraph (A) with respect to nationals of a program country (as designated under subsection (c) of this section), if the Secretary of State finds that the program country_

I14(i) is making progress toward ensuring that passports meeting the requirement of subparagraph (A) are generally available to its nationals; and

I14(ii) has taken appropriate measures to protect against misuse of passports the country has issued that do not meet the requirement of subparagraph (A).

I79(4) Executes immigration forms

I12The alien before the time of such admission completes such immigration form as the Attorney General shall establish.

I79(5) Entry into the United States

