I89. Children born outside the United States and residing permanently in the United States; conditions under which citizenship automatically acquired

I11(a) A child born outside of the United States automatically becomes a citizen of the United States when all of the following conditions have been fulfilled:

I12(1) At least one parent of the child is a citizen of the United States, whether by birth or naturalization.

I12(2) The child is under the age of eighteen years.

I12(3) The child is residing in the United States in the legal and physical custody of the citizen parent pursuant to a lawful admission for permanent residence.

